library(wesanderson)
lipdata <-read_excel("C:/Users/jessi/Desktop/Feed trial samplings_R.xlsx") #here i am assigning a name to my dataset
lipdata$sampling <-factor(lipdata$sampling)
lipdata$diet<-factor(lipdata$diet)
lipdata$tank<-factor(lipdata$tank)




arcsine_transform <- function(x) {
  asin(sqrt(x / 100))}  # Transform percentage to proportion and apply arcsine

lipdata_transformed <- lipdata %>%
  mutate(across(c(26, 28, 30, 32, 36, 37, 41), ~ arcsine_transform(.)))

s0<-lipdata_transformed %>% 
  filter(sampling=="0") #filtering data for basal sampling (sampling 0)

s1<-lipdata_transformed %>% 
  filter(sampling=="1") #filtering data for sampling 1

s2<-lipdata_transformed %>% 
  filter(sampling=="2") #filtering data for sampling 2

  geom_boxplot(color = "black", fill = "white") +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.2, alpha = 0.6, size = 1) +

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

# Prepare data: exclude "X" and set desired order
filtered_data <- lipdata %>%
  filter(diet2 != "X") %>%
  mutate(diet2 = factor(diet2, levels = c("COM", "100KO", "75KO", "50KO", "25KO", "0KO")))

# Plot
ggplot(filtered_data, aes(x = diet2, y = dblipwf)) +
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.4, color = "black", fill = "white") +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.15, alpha = 0.6, size = 1) +
  stat_summary(fun = median, geom = "text", aes(label = round(..y.., 2)),
               vjust = -0.5, color = "black", size = 4) +
  coord_cartesian( ylim = c(14,32)) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    text = element_text(size = 14),
    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 16, hjust = 0.5),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0, vjust = 1),
    legend.position = "none"
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Total lipid in whole fish",
    x = "Diet",
    y = "Lipid content (%)"
  )
